t: To the chief Musician upon Shushan–eduth, Michtam of David, to teach; when he strove with Aram–naharaim and with Aram–zobah, when Joab returned, and smote of Edom in the valley of salt twelve thousand.
O*p God, thou hast cast us off, thou hast scattered us, thou hast been displeased; O turn thyself to us again.
Thou*p hast made the earth to tremble; thou hast broken it: heal the breaches thereof; for it shaketh.
Thou*p hast shewed thy people hard things: thou hast made us to drink the wine of astonishment.
Thou*p hast given a banner to them that fear thee, that it may be displayed because of the truth. Selah.
That*p thy beloved may be delivered; save with thy right hand, and hear me.
God*p hath spoken in his holiness; I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem, and mete out the valley of Succoth.
Gilead*p is mine, and Manasseh is mine; Ephraim also is the strength of mine head; Judah is my lawgiver;
Moab*p is my washpot; over Edom will I cast out my shoe: Philistia, triumph thou because of me.
Who*p will bring me into the strong city? who will lead me into Edom?
Wilt*p not thou, O God, which hadst cast us off? and thou, O God, which didst not go out with our armies?
Give*p us help from trouble: for vain is the help of man.
Through*p God we shall do valiantly: for he it is that shall tread down our enemies.
